llowing, creating permanent lockup unless special recovery exists.","paths":["Subvault holds asset X","Governance disallows X for that subvault","Any later pull path calling `modifySubvaultBalance(subvault, X, negative)` reverts with `NotAllowedAsset`"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Redeem hook can be griefed by dusting disallowed subvaults","locations":["hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:19","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:24","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:39","managers/RiskManager.sol:242","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:178","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:194"],"claim":"`BasicRedeemHook` treats raw ERC20 balances in all subvaults as liquid and tries to pull from any subvault with positive balance. If a subvault is not allowed for that asset, `hookPullAssets` reaches `modifySubvaultBalance` and reverts with `NotAllowedAsset`.","impact":"An attacker can dust tokens into a disallowed subvault and cause redemption batch handling to revert, creating permissionless DoS on affected redeem flows using this hook.","paths":["Attacker transfers dust of redeem asset A to subvault S that disallows A","Hook counts S balance as liquid and attempts pull during redeem processing","RiskManager rejects pull for disallowed asset, reverting batch handling"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Deposit accounting assumes exact ERC20 transfers and breaks on fee-on-transfer tokens","locations":["libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:46","queues/DepositQueue.sol:77","queues/DepositQueue.sol:91","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:14","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:18"],"claim":"ERC20 receive paths trust requested amount and do not check actual token delta after transfer. For taxed/deflationary tokens, internal accounting and minted shares are based on nominal amount while actual received amount is lower.","impact":"If such assets are supported, the protocol can mint excess shares versus r