rt (pending deposit cancellation, redeem batch handling, vault balance updates), creating stuck accounting and realistic fund lockup for that asset.","paths":["Privileged actor removes an asset still used by queues/positions","Subsequent flows call `RiskManager.convertToShares(asset, ...)`","`oracle.getReport(asset)` reverts `UnsupportedAsset`, bricking settlement/cancelation paths"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Permissionless claiming allows third parties to impose targeted-lockup timing on victims","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:234","queues/DepositQueue.sol:120","managers/ShareManager.sol:180","managers/ShareManager.sol:229"],"claim":"`ShareModule.claimShares(account)` and `DepositQueue.claim(account)` are callable by anyone for arbitrary users. When claim mints shares, `ShareManager.mint` sets `accounts[account].lockedUntil = block.timestamp + targetedLockup`, letting third parties choose when that lock window starts.","impact":"If `targetedLockup` is enabled, attackers can front-run user actions and force lock activation at adverse times, temporarily blocking victim transfers/burns (including previously-held active shares) and causing targeted denial-of-use.","paths":["Victim has claimable deposit shares and `targetedLockup` is non-zero","Attacker calls `claimShares(victim)` or `DepositQueue.claim(victim)` before victim’s planned transfer/redeem","Claim mints and refreshes `lockedUntil`, making victim’s next transfer/burn revert until expiry"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Signature queues bypass configured deposit/redeem fee hooks","locations":["queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:21","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:22","queues/DepositQueue.sol:167","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:100"],"claim":"Standard queues apply fee logic via `FeeManager.calculateDepositFee` / `calculateRedeemFee` during report handling or redeem r