ary.sol:31"],"claim":"`_pushAssets` and `_pullAssets` update risk accounting using the requested `value` and then perform token transfers without measuring actual received deltas. Fee-on-transfer/deflationary behavior can move less than `value` while accounting assumes full movement.","impact":"Subvault exposure and available-liquidity accounting can drift from real balances, causing limit checks to rely on inflated values and creating later pull/redeem failures or effective shortfalls.","paths":["Push a taxed token from vault to subvault via `_pushAssets`; risk state increases by full `value` while subvault receives less.","Subsequent pulls/redeems rely on overstated accounting and fail when trying to source missing tokens."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-019","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Payable ERC20 queue entrypoints can permanently trap accidental ETH","locations":["queues/DepositQueue.sol:59","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:11","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:13","libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:40"],"claim":"For non-ETH assets, `receiveAssets` does not enforce `msg.value == 0`. Multiple queue entrypoints are `payable`, so extra ETH is accepted while logic continues with ERC20 accounting only.","impact":"Users/integrators can accidentally send ETH alongside ERC20 queue calls and have it stranded in queue contracts with no recovery path.","paths":["Call an ERC20 queue function with nonzero `msg.value`.","ERC20 transfer path executes successfully and the ETH remains stuck in the queue contract."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-020","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Anyone can steal pending deposit allocations via unrestricted `mintAllocatedShares`","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:212","managers/ShareManager.sol:214","managers/ShareManager.sol:219"],"claim":"`mintAllocatedShares(address,uint256)` is externally callable with no `onlyQueue`/`onlyVault`/role restriction. Any account can co