claim":"`DepositQueue.canBeRemoved()` only checks processing progress (`handledIndices == timestamps.length()`), not whether users have actually claimed. After `removeQueue`, claim execution reaches `ShareManager.mint` through `mintAllocatedShares`, but `mint` enforces `onlyVaultOrQueue` and the removed queue no longer satisfies `hasQueue`, so claims from that queue revert.","impact":"A privileged queue-removal action can strand claimable deposits in an unclaimable state, causing practical permanent lockup of user entitlements from that queue.","paths":["Deposits are handled and shares are allocated, but some users have not yet called claim","Authorized actor removes the deposit queue once `canBeRemoved()` returns true","User later calls `DepositQueue.claim(account)`","`mintAllocatedShares` invokes `mint`, `onlyVaultOrQueue` fails because the queue was removed, and claim reverts"],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-102","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Native-ETH sentinel asset configuration can DoS redeem liquidity checks","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:150","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:11","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:35","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:178","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:18","libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:20"],"claim":"The system supports a native-ETH sentinel asset in `TransferLibrary`, but redeem liquidity paths call `IERC20(asset).balanceOf(...)` (`ShareModule.getLiquidAssets` when no hook, and `BasicRedeemHook.getLiquidAssets/callHook`). For the ETH sentinel this is not a valid ERC20 target and can revert during ABI decode/call.","impact":"If a queue is configured with the ETH sentinel asset, redeem handling and signature-redeem prechecks can become uncallable, causing withdrawal denial and potential lockup for affected users.","paths":["Configure/create redeem flow for `TransferLibrary.ETH` asset","Call `RedeemQueue.handleBatches` or `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem`","Flow calls `vault.getLiquidAssets()` and executes ERC20 `balanceOf` against ETH sentinel","Call reverts and redeem processing cannot proceed"],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-103","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Role fallback in `onlyQueueOrRole` is broken for non-queue callers","locations":["managers/RiskManager.sol:49","modules/ShareModule.sol:56","modules/ShareModule.sol:57","managers/RiskManager.sol:206","managers/RiskManager.sol:224"],"claim":"`onlyQueueOrRole` first evaluates `IShareModule(vault).hasQueue(caller)`. `hasQueue` calls `IQueue(caller).asset()` unconditionally, which can revert for EOAs/multisigs/non-queue contracts before the role check runs. As a result, role-authorized operators cannot reliably call queue-or-role guarded functions unless they are queue contracts.","impact":"Intended emergency/reconciliation operations (`modifyPendingAssets`, `modifyVaultBalance`) may be inaccessible to governance/ops role holders during incidents, prolonging accounting drift and operational disruption.","paths":["Grant `MODIFY_PENDING_ASSETS_ROLE` or `MODIFY_VAULT_BALANCE_ROLE` to an operator account that is not a queue contract","Operator calls `modifyPendingAssets` or `modifyVaultBalance`","`hasQueue(caller)` reverts while trying `IQueue(caller).asset()`","Execution reverts before role fallback is evaluated"],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-201","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Tokenized lockup is bypassable via auto-claim ordering in `_update`","locations":["managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:47","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:49","managers/ShareManager.sol:229","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:98"],"claim":"`TokenizedShareManager._update` performs `updateChecks(from,to)` before `claimShares(from)`. If `claimShares` mints pending deposit shares, `mint` sets a fresh `lockedUntil` only after checks, and the same update still completes transfer/burn.","impact":"Users can move or redeem newly claimed shares immediately in the same transaction, bypassing targeted lockup/cooldown enforcement.","paths":["User has claimable deposit shares and `targetedLockup > 0`.","User calls redeem/transfer that triggers `_update(from, ..., value)`.","`updateChecks` passes using pre-claim lock state, then `claimShares(from)` mints and sets new lock.","Operation still burns/transfers those freshly claimed shares in the same call."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-202","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Signature deposits bypass depositor whitelist checks on the caller","locations":["queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:12","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:21","queues/DepositQueue.sol:69"],"claim":"`SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` never verifies `isDepositorWhitelisted(order.caller, ...)`; it validates signatures and then mints to `order.recipient`. The whitelist gate in `ShareManager.updateChecks` applies to the recipient on mint, not the caller providing funds.","impact":"If operators rely on depositor-side whitelist restrictions, non-whitelisted callers can still route deposits through signature flow by directing shares to an allowed recipient, weakening access-control/compliance assumptions.","paths":["A non-whitelisted caller obtains valid consensus signatures for an order with a whitelisted recipient.","Caller submits `SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` and transfers assets.","Mint succeeds for recipient without any caller-whitelist verification path."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-203","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Blacklist is not enforced for transfer recipients","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:131","managers/ShareManager.sol:134"],"claim":"In transfer flow (`from != 0 && to != 0`), `updateChecks` verifies blacklist status for `from` but does not check whether `to` is blacklisted.","impact":"Blacklisted accounts can still receive shares, violating send/receive blacklist expectations and enabling policy bypass.","paths":["A non-blacklisted holder transfers shares to a blacklisted address.","Transfer passes because only sender blacklist status is checked."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-204","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"First report for a newly supported asset is always marked suspicious","locations":["oracles/Oracle.sol:199","oracles/Oracle.sol:116","oracles/Oracle.sol:124"],"claim":"When an asset has no prior report (`prevPriceD18 == 0`), `_validatePrice` always returns `(true, true)`. As a result, `submitReports` records the report as suspicious and skips `vault.handleReport`; progressing that asset requires a separate `acceptReport` call.","impact":"Newly added assets have a hard operational dependency on `ACCEPT_REPORT_ROLE`; if that path is unavailable, queue/risk processing for the asset can remain stuck.","paths":["Governance adds a new supported asset with empty report history.","Reporter submits the first price via `submitReports`; it is flagged suspicious and not forwarded to vault handling.","Without a successful `acceptReport`, asset-specific processing does not advance."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-301","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Queue creator can pick queue proxy admin and later upgrade into privileged malicious queue logic","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:192","factories/Factory.sol:115","managers/ShareManager.sol:223","managers/ShareManager.sol:240"],"claim":"`createQueue` takes arbitrary `owner` and forwards it to `Factory.create`, where that address becomes queue upgrade authority. The vault then trusts queue address identity for privileged paths (`onlyQueue`/`onlyVaultOrQueue`), so an attacker-controlled queue admin can upgrade queue code and execute privileged share operations.","impact":"A holder of CREATE_QUEUE_ROLE can escalate to effective mint/burn control through queue upgradeability, enabling share inflation, victim share burning, and downstream fund theft/insolvency.","paths":["Obtain CREATE_QUEUE_ROLE","Call `createQueue(..., owner=attacker, ...)`","Upgrade created queue proxy to malicious implementation","Use malicious queue code to call privileged share/risk functions as a registered queue"],"round":9,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-302","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Signature redeem queue cannot receive ETH transferred from vault hook flow","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:264","libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:28","queues/SignatureQueue.sol:9","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:13"],"claim":"Redeem flows send assets from vault to queue via `TransferLibrary.sendAssets`; for native ETH this uses `sendValue`. `SignatureRedeemQueue` (via `SignatureQueue`) does not implement a payable `receive`/fallback, so ETH transfer to the queue reverts.","impact":"ETH-configured signature redeem queues become unexecutable (hard DoS of signature redemptions for that asset).","paths":["Configure a signature redeem queue for native-ETH sentinel asset","Call `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem(...)`","Vault executes `callHook` and attempts ETH transfer to queue","Transfer reverts because queue cannot receive plain ETH"],"round":9,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Lido deposit hook forwards ETH to wstETH address in WETH/ETH branch","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Non-reportable as written: this is the intended Lido wstETH integration path (sending ETH to wstETH contract to mint wrapped shares), and existing tests exercise ETH/WETH branches without indicating protocol-level loss semantics."},{"title":"OwnedCustomVerifier initializer lacks array length validation","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Rejected as non-reportable: mismatched array lengths only cause initialization revert for malformed init payloads, with no realistic fund-loss, privilege-escalation, or persistent DoS vector in normal atomic proxy initialization flow."}]}
